//
// test/lex/strings/unterminated.test — fail fixture for an
// unterminated string literal. Per `lang.ebnf §13` a `string_char`
// excludes literal newline; an opening `"` followed by EOL or EOF
// without a closing `"` is a lex error.
//
// FR-037 + diagnostic-output.contract.md "Mandatory diagnostic-string
// fixtures" lock the message text: `unterminated string literal`.
// Renaming or weakening this string later requires a contract
// amendment + this fixture's update in the same change.
//
// `not %nslc ...` makes lit expect a non-zero exit code; the
// `nslc -emit=tokens` contract maps a lex error to exit 1 with the
// diagnostic on stderr and NO tokens on stdout.

// RUN: not %nslc -emit=tokens %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s

"hello
// CHECK: error: unterminated string literal
